MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The previous server.js had several issues that prevented login from
working even after the auth flow was fixed:

1. The seed only created a single user with email='teacher@test.com'
   and no username. Since RightPanel.js submits 'username' (not email),
   that seed could never be matched at login.

2. CORS origin was hard-coded to http://localhost:3000 with no env
   override, making non-default frontend ports impossible.

3. The DB lifecycle code was wrapped in a long .then() chain mixing
   sync, seed, and listen — hard to follow, and any failure printed
   only 'Database connection failed' with no exit code.

This commit:
- Wraps startup in an async IIFE with try/catch and process.exit(1)
  on failure so the user immediately knows something went wrong.
- Calls a separate seedDefaultUsers() helper that creates two users
  the login form can actually accept:
    admin  / Admin@1234   (HOI/ADMINISTRATOR)
    sysdev / Sysdev@1234  (SYSTEM DEVELOPER)
- All seed values can be overridden via DEFAULT_ADMIN_USERNAME etc.
- CORS origin reads FRONTEND_ORIGIN from env (default localhost:3000).
- PORT reads from env, defaulting to 5000 (matches frontend axios base).
- On successful boot, prints a banner with the URL, DB dialect, CORS
  origin, and the seeded credentials so the user knows exactly what
  to put in the login form.
